&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONSULTANT ORTHOPAEDIC HIP SURGEON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited to apply for the above post for the Orthopaedic and Rheumatology Directorate at the Nuffield Orthopaeidic Centre, Windmill Road, Oxford, OX3 7HE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Consultant Hip Surgeon&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Nuffield Orthopaedic Centre, part of Oxford University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust would like to appoint a Consultant Orthopaedic Surgeon as part of a planned expansion to join a dynamic team of consultant hip and knee orthopaedic surgeons.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are expanding our service and have a vacancy in the Trauma and Orthopaedic team for a consultant orthopaedic hip surgeon with a special subspeciality interest in the treatment of periprosthetic joint infection and the perioperative care of complex arthroplasty patients. The appointee will be expected to work flexibly within the hip and knee team. They will be expected to participate in the on-call rota. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;All applications for consultant posts must either be on the General Medical Council’s Specialist Register or be within six months of obtaining their CCT at the time of interview.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the interest of equal opportunities, we want to make sure that information about candidates is provided in the same format so all applicants should fill in the standard application form on the NHS Jobs website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKaren BarkerJob titleClinical DirectorEmail addresskaren.barker@ouh.nhs.ukTelephone number38080&lt;/p&gt;
